mentions.context: SPBv [9] is a benchmark for RDF archives that consists of a data generator based on the Semantic Publishing Benchmark (SPB) [16] from the Linked Data Benchmark Council (LDBC) [7].
EvoGen [15] is a benchmark based on the LUBM [8] data generator extended to support evolving RDF scenarios.

Both EvoGen [15] and SPBv [9] provide SPARQL queries of varied nature, but only focus on the generation of one restrictive type of datasets, which have not been evaluated realism, e.g., via the coherence metric [6].

Due to being a relatively new area in RDF data management, we only account for three benchmarks tailored for RDF archiving in the literature: EvoGen [15], BEAR [1], and SPBv [9].
